<task id="054" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4">
  <metadata>
    <title>B-5: BFF workspace-layout updates — PUT + If-Match ETag OR PATCH + JSON Patch (concurrency safety)</title>
    <phase>Phase 5 — Substantive code changes</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>053</dependencies>
    <blocks>none</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, deploy</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Tag 'bff-api'; modifies endpoint semantics (concurrency safety); §10 Placement Justification REQUIRED; depends on 053 ModifiedOn field. Per Step 3.5.5 decision tree, FULL rigor.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>same file as task 053 (WorkspaceLayoutEndpoints.cs + WorkspaceLayoutDtos.cs + WorkspaceLayoutService.cs); 054 builds on 053's ModifiedOn field for ETag derivation. MUST sequence after 053.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add concurrency safety to BFF workspace-layout updates. Pick ONE of two designs at task start
    (per OC-R4-08): (a) KEEP PUT semantics and add `If-Match` ETag header validation (ETag derived from
    `modifiedOn` rowversion exposed by task 053); OR (b) introduce a separate PATCH endpoint using
    RFC 6902 JSON Patch. Decision criterion: client-side complexity tradeoff. Two concurrent edits MUST
    result in the second being rejected (412 Precondition Failed) OR merged (JSON Patch). Record §10
    Placement Justification. Verify publish-size ≤60 MB.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET 8 Minimal API developer with concurrency-safety design experience. Familiar with HTTP
    semantics (RFC 7232 If-Match, RFC 6902 JSON Patch). Bias toward the simpler client-side option;
    document the tradeoff at task start before coding.
  </role>

  <goal>
    (a) BFF workspace-layout update endpoint supports concurrency safety via either: PUT + `If-Match`
    ETag validation (412 on mismatch) OR PATCH + RFC 6902 JSON Patch (server-side merge); (b) ETag value
    derived from `modifiedOn` (provided by task 053); (c) frontend write path adapted to send `If-Match`
    header or JSON Patch body; (d) integration test: 2 concurrent edits — second rejected with 412 (PUT)
    or merged (PATCH); (e) §10 Placement Justification entry; (f) `dotnet publish` ≤60 MB compressed
    verified.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-08 (B-5) + plan §4 Phase 5 + OC-R4-08 (decision at task time): workspace layouts are
      multi-edit surfaces (the Manage pane shows them all; multiple operators or even the same operator
      across tabs can edit concurrently). Today the BFF accepts the last write unconditionally — silently
      losing concurrent edits. Adding concurrency safety is a §10 BFF addition (governance applies).

      OC-R4-08 explicitly left the design choice open: PUT + If-Match (simpler client, no merge logic)
      vs PATCH + JSON Patch (richer semantics, server-side merge possible, more client complexity to
      generate the patch document). The decision criterion is client-side complexity tradeoff — pick at
      task start based on whether the frontend already has a diff/patch story or needs to build one.

      Task 053 (B-4) exposes `modifiedOn` on the DTO; this task (054) consumes that field as the ETag
      value source (or rowversion source) — that's why 054 must sequence after 053.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Workspace/WorkspaceLayoutEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Workspace/WorkspaceLayoutDtos.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/WorkspaceLayoutService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Filters/WorkspaceLayoutAuthorizationFilter.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Integration/Workspace/WorkspaceLayoutEndpointTests.cs</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/hooks/useWorkspaceLayouts.ts (consolidated by task 051 — write path)</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/ManageWorkspacesPane.tsx (write trigger)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Minimal API only. Extend the existing endpoint group; do NOT introduce controllers.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint filters: PATCH endpoint (if chosen) inherits the existing `WorkspaceLayoutAuthorizationFilter` filter pipeline. Filters fire BEFORE concurrency-check handler logic.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — extend `WorkspaceLayoutService`; do NOT introduce a new service.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF in-process placement. No AI coupling. §10 still applies to this BFF addition. CRUD code MUST NOT inject `IOpenAiClient` / `IPlaybookService` (N/A here).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Publish hygiene — verify `dotnet publish` ≤60 MB compressed. If adding a JSON Patch library (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.JsonPatch` or `Marvin.JsonPatch.Dynamic`), measure the publish-size impact carefully.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">CLAUDE.md §10 Placement Justification REQUIRED in PR notes citing `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` decision criteria.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">CVE check (NFR-09): any new NuGet package (JSON Patch lib if PATCH path chosen) MUST report 0 new HIGH-severity findings via `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Design decision (OC-R4-08): pick PUT+If-Match OR PATCH+JSON-Patch at task start. Record decision + rationale in `notes/b5-design-decision.md` BEFORE writing code.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">ETag derivation (if PUT+If-Match chosen): use `modifiedOn` value as the ETag (weak ETag W/"timestamp" is acceptable; strong ETag from row version is preferred if available). Per RFC 7232.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">JSON Patch (if PATCH chosen): conform to RFC 6902 (operations: add, remove, replace, move, copy, test). Server MUST validate patch operations against the layout schema before applying.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Concurrency rejection response: 412 Precondition Failed for PUT+If-Match mismatch. PATCH may return 412 (server detects conflict) OR succeed via merge — document semantics in the OpenAPI annotation.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Client write path must be updated to consume the new semantic — either send `If-Match` from the cached layout's `modifiedOn` OR generate a JSON Patch document on save.</constraint>
  </constraints>

