  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor declaration">Output rigor declaration: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — bff-api tag, concurrency semantics change, §10 Placement Justification REQUIRED. Step 9.5 quality gates MANDATORY.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Confirm dependency 053 landed">Verify task 053 (B-4 ModifiedOn) is ✅ in TASK-INDEX.md. The DTO `ModifiedOn` field is the ETag source. If 053 is pending, BLOCK.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Design decision (OC-R4-08)">Read the spec note + RFC 6902 / RFC 7232 external refs. Inspect the frontend write path (in the consolidated hook from task 051 and ManageWorkspacesPane). Decide: PUT+If-Match OR PATCH+JSON-Patch. Criterion: client-side complexity. Write decision + rationale in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/b5-design-decision.md` BEFORE coding.</step>
    <step order="3" name="§10 Placement Justification">Draft Placement Justification per `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`. Stash in PR notes: CRUD-side endpoint semantics change; no AI coupling; ADR-013 in-process correct; publish-size impact known (zero new packages if PUT+If-Match; JSON Patch lib if PATCH).</step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement endpoint (PUT+If-Match path)">If PUT+If-Match chosen: extend `WorkspaceLayoutEndpoints.cs` PUT handler to read `If-Match` header, compare against current layout's `modifiedOn` value (or rowversion). Return 412 Precondition Failed on mismatch. Add ETag response header on read (GET emits ETag from `modifiedOn`). Update OpenAPI annotations (`Produces`, `ProducesProblem(412)`).</step>
    <step order="4b" name="Implement endpoint (PATCH+JSON-Patch path)">If PATCH+JSON-Patch chosen: add `MapPatch("/{id}", PatchLayoutAsync)` to the endpoint group with the existing filter pipeline. Accept `JsonPatchDocument&lt;WorkspaceLayoutDto&gt;` body. Validate operations + apply to current entity + persist. Add the NuGet package if not present (`Microsoft.AspNetCore.JsonPatch` is the canonical choice; verify publish-size impact &lt;1 MB).</step>
    <step order="5" name="Service layer update">Extend `WorkspaceLayoutService.cs` to support the chosen concurrency check (rowversion read+compare, or patch-apply with merge). Keep the existing service signature; ADD a new method if needed rather than overloading the existing one.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Integration tests">Edit `WorkspaceLayoutEndpointTests.cs` to add the concurrency-conflict test: (a) fetch layout (record ETag/modifiedOn); (b) make a successful update; (c) attempt second update with the OLD ETag; (d) assert 412 (PUT) or assert merge behavior (PATCH). Also add: ETag round-trip test (GET → update with returned ETag → success).</step>
    <step order="7" name="Frontend write-path adaptation">Update `useWorkspaceLayouts.ts` (consolidated by task 051) write path to either send `If-Match` from the cached layout's `modifiedOn` OR generate a JSON Patch document. Update `ManageWorkspacesPane.tsx` to surface a clear "Edit conflict — refresh and retry" UX on 412 responses.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Build verification (server)">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Verify 0 errors / 0 new warnings. Run `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~WorkspaceLayout"`. Verify all pass including new concurrency tests.</step>
    <step order="9" name="Build verification (client)">Run `tsc --noEmit` + `npm run build` for `@spaarke/ai-widgets` + SpaarkeAi. Verify 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates">Invoke `code-review` skill and `adr-check` skill. Verify ADR-001/008/010/013/029 compliance; verify §10 BFF hygiene enforcement passes.</step>
    <step order="10" name="Publish-size check (NFR-01)">Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Verify ≤60 MB compressed. Record delta vs baseline. PATCH path: confirm the JSON Patch lib adds &lt;1 MB.</step>
    <step order="11" name="CVE check (NFR-09)">Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`. Verify 0 new HIGH-severity findings. Important if a new lib was added.</step>
    <step order="12" name="Deploy">Deploy BFF via `bff-deploy` skill. Deploy SpaarkeAi via `code-page-deploy` skill.</step>
    <step order="13" name="Smoke verification">In SpaarkeAi → Manage Workspaces: open the same layout in two browser tabs, edit + save tab 1 → confirm tab 2's subsequent save fails with a clear "edit conflict" message.</step>
    <step order="14" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Edit `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: flip task 054 status 🔲 → ✅.</step>
    <step order="15" name="Document deviations">If the chosen design encountered surprises (e.g., merge semantics for PATCH proved tricky), document in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/` for R4 lessons-learned.</step>
  </steps>

