  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given two concurrent edits to the same workspace layout, When both are submitted, Then the second submission is REJECTED with HTTP 412 (PUT+If-Match) OR merged successfully (PATCH+JSON-Patch) — FR-08 acceptance.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the §10 rule, When the PR is opened, Then PR notes contain a Placement Justification entry citing `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` decision criteria.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given OC-R4-08 decision criterion, When the design decision is made, Then `notes/b5-design-decision.md` documents the choice + rationale BEFORE code is written.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the frontend write path, When a concurrent-edit conflict occurs, Then the user sees a clear "edit conflict — refresh and retry" message in the Manage pane.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given NFR-01 publish-size, When `dotnet publish -c Release` is run, Then compressed publish size ≤60 MB and delta vs baseline is recorded.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given NFR-09 CVE policy, When `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` is run, Then 0 new HIGH-severity findings are reported (especially relevant if a JSON Patch NuGet package was added).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All unit + integration tests pass (`dotnet test`); concurrency-conflict test is among the passing set.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    OPEN at task start (OC-R4-08): PUT+If-Match vs PATCH+JSON-Patch. Default recommendation: PUT+If-Match
    if the frontend already sends full layout JSON on save (no patch document needed); PATCH+JSON-Patch
    if the frontend wants partial updates (e.g., reorder sections without resending full layout). The
    Manage pane today likely sends full JSON — so PUT+If-Match is the simpler answer unless task 052
    (renderer interface) or a future host needs partial updates.

    External refs (per spec): RFC 6902 https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6902 ; RFC 7232 If-Match
    https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7232 . Read at least the relevant sections (RFC 7232 §3.1
    If-Match; RFC 6902 §4 operations) before coding.

    Same-file warning: task 053 modifies WorkspaceLayoutEndpoints.cs + WorkspaceLayoutDtos.cs +
    WorkspaceLayoutService.cs. Task 054 modifies the SAME FILES. Sequence is enforced via dependency.
  </notes>

